Description.val:
FY 2012 funding totals include $15.0M appropriated for Overseas Contingency Operations. (ATP Program)

This line item funds multiple modifications that apply to weapon systems funded at less than $2 million per year as well as weapon systems with much greater budgets.  The overall goal of the modifications budgeted in FY13 is to enhance capability and improve reliability and maintainability.  A major modification budgeted in FY13 is The Family of Advanced Beyond Line-of-Sight Terminals (FAB-T) Increment 1 program that will provide Extremely High Frequency (EHF) voice and data military satellite communications (MILSATCOM) for nuclear and conventional forces as well as airborne and ground command posts with connectivity to MILSTAR  and Advanced EHF satellites.
